-- American States Water Beats Analyst Estimates on Rising Sales
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2012-08-06T20:50:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-06/american-states-water-beats-analyst-estimates-on-rising-sales.html
American States Water Company (AWR) , which
provides water to 255,000 customers in California, reported
earnings that exceeded analysts’ expectations as second-quarter
sales rose 4 percent.  American States, based in San Dimas, California, reported
net income of $15.1 million, or 79 cents a share, compared with
$12.7 million, or 68 cents, a year ago, the company said in a
statement today. Earning were 15 cents higher than the average
of four analysts’  estimates  compiled by Bloomberg.  Sales were $114.3 million, up from $109.8 million a year
earlier.  The company’s shares rose 0.8 percent to $41.78 at the
close in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
